SIMPLE: dissuasion
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Dissuasion
<hw>Dis*sua"sion</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>dissuasio</ets>: cf. F. <ets>dissuasion</ets>. See
<er>Dissuade</er>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>The act of dissuading;
exhortation against a thing; dehortation.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>In spite of all the <qex>dissuasions</qex> of his friends.</q>
<rj><qau>Boyle.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>A motive or consideration tending to dissuade; a
dissuasive.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Dissuasive</ent>⟦br⟧
